Breast Cancer Detection Machine Learning Model Building¶

classifcation->>> specify which of the k categories some input belongs to.¶

supervised->>>>data is labeled data(output is given)¶

To build the best model, we have to train and test the dataset with multiple Machine Learning algorithms then we can find the best ML model.

SVM(support vector machine)¶

SVM is a binary classification model

In [12]:
#support vector machine
from sklearn.svm import SVC
svc_classifier = SVC()
svc_classifier.fit(X_train,Y_train) #train the model
y_pred_svc=svc_classifier.predict(X_test) 
print("Accuracy:",metrics.accuracy_score(Y_test, y_pred_svc))

Accuracy: 0.9298245614035088
In [13]:
# Train with Standard scaled Data
svc_classifier2 = SVC()
svc_classifier2.fit(X_train_sc,Y_train) #train the model
y_pred_svc_sc=svc_classifier2.predict(X_test_sc) #test the model
print("Accuracy:",metrics.accuracy_score(Y_test, y_pred_svc_sc)) # accuracy

Accuracy: 0.9736842105263158

precision---> هو اتوقع كام حاجه صح من كل فئه (TP/(TP+FP))¶

Recall --->نسبة الملاحظات الإيجابية المتوقعة بشكل صحيح إلى جميع الملاحظات في الفصل الفعلي(TP/(TP+FN)¶

f1-score--->average of precision and recall¶

In [27]:
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, f1_score, precision_score, recall_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix
#Precision
print("Precision:",metrics.precision_score(Y_test,y_pred_adb ,average=None) )

#Recall (>0.5  good model)
print("Precision:",metrics.recall_score(Y_test, y_pred_adb ,average=None))

#f1-score
print("F1-Score:",metrics.f1_score(Y_test, y_pred_adb ,average=None))
